<item>
            <title>[LU-18680] Improve syntaxes for some nodemap lproc entries</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18680</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;idmap&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;exports&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;ranges&lt;/tt&gt; are nodemap related entries visible with get_param of nodemap_info. There are all list of elements, with a YAML syntax.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are 2 issues:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There is a syntax bug in &apos;&lt;tt&gt;idmap&lt;/tt&gt;&apos; when only gid or projid is set, but not uid mapping.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When the list is empty, the output is on 3 lines, with a blank one, instead of a more simple &apos;[]&apos;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Let&apos;s fix that.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
